isions  discovery networks us  holdings  discovery networks international  group nine media  discovery education  history   hostage crisis  see also  references  external links corporate governance and historyedit nbcuniversal executive david zaslav was named president and ceo on november   in addition to zaslav current executives include adria alpert romm chief human resources  global diversity officer bruce campbell chief development distribution  legal officer  bill goodwyn president  ceo discovery education paul guyardo chief commercial officer john honeycutt chief technology officer david leavy chief corporate operations and communications officer jeanbriac jb perrette president discovery networks international gunnar wiedenfels chief financial officer  prior to september   dcis ownership consisted of three shareholders discovery holding company advancenewhouse communications which is owned with advance publications john s hendricks the companys founder on september   discovery holding company completed a restructuring plan discovery holdings ascent media business was spun off and the remaining businesses discovery communications llc and advancenewhouse communications were combined into a new holding company discovery communications inc the new fully public company and trades on the nasdaq stock market under the symbols disca discb and disck sec filings are submitted by the discovery holding company in may  the company announced a special dividend of shares of the companys series c common stock payable to holders of record of the companys series a common stock series b common stock and series c common stock as of the close of business on july   as a result of the dividend each holder of a share of the companys series a common stock series b common stock or series c common stock will receive one additional share of the companys series c common stock on or about august   through group nine media discovery connects with millennial audiences through digitalfirst brands nowthis thrillist the dodo source fed studios and seeker which has  billion streams per month in may  discovery and liberty global announced an agreement to form a  joint venture to acquire allmedia a producer and distributor of tv programming liberty global and discovery communications paid approximately  million for a  stake in lions gate entertainment group in november  liberty ceo mike fries joined the lions gate board of directors as part of the acquisition divisionsedit dci operates its businesses in the following groups discovery networks us discovery networks international discovery studios group discovery digital media and discovery education discovery networks usedit the companys namesake and flagship brand discovery channel first launched on june   in  discovery channels owners acquired the learning channel in october  discovery launched several new spinoff networks including animal planet and the digital cable channels discovery kids discovery travel  living discovery civilization and science channel this was followed by the  purchase of a  stake in travel channel and the  launches of discovery en español discovery wings and discovery health channel also in  discovery acquired a stake in the struggling cbs eye on people channel discovery eventually acquired the remainder of cbss stake leading to its january  relaunch as discovery people the network quietly folded in  being replaced by other discovery channels on providers on september   discovery communications bought the health channel and announced that it would be rebranded as fittv in  discovery relaunched discovery civilization as discovery times as part of a joint venture with the new york times in june  coinciding with discoverys th anniversary the company launched a  high definition channel known as discovery hd theater in march  discovery sold its stake in travel channel back to cox communications in exchange for the stake in discovery that cox owned cox would later sell the controlling interest in the channel to scripps networks interactive in  in june  discovery home was replaced by planet green a network devoted primarily to environmentalism and ecological living on january   discovery announced that it had entered into a joint venture with oprah winfreys harpo productions to relaunch discovery health as a new service own the oprah winfrey network in  in  discovery times was relaunched as investigation discovery a new brand that would be dedicated to true crime programs and documentaries on april   discovery announced a joint venture with hasbro to relaunch discovery kids as a new youth and familyoriented entertainment channel the channel ultimately named the hub launched on october   after multiple delays own officially launched on january   on october   due to the wider rollout of highdefinition feeds for mainstream cable channels hd theater was replaced by velocity a new upscale maleoriented channel focusing primarily on automotivethemed programming on may   planet green which had begun to abandon its original concept by  due to poor viewership was relaunched as destination america in october  discovery acquired controlling interest in the hub then hub network from hasbro and rebranded it as discovery family in december  discovery launched discovery go a tv everywhere service offering access to live streaming and ondemand content from discovery communications cable networks holdingsedit channel launch date us households as of august  notes discovery channel   million flagship network tlc   million acquired by discovery communications in may  previously known as the learning channel animal planet   million investigation discovery   million formerly discovery times discovery civilization own   million joint venture ownership with harpo productions velocity   million formerly discovery hd theater and hd theater science   million discovery family   million initially launched as discovery kids in  relaunched as the hub in  renamed hub network on  and