 adventure crime and investigation health and kids it also develops and sells curriculumbased education products and services such as an online suite of curriculumbased video on demand vod tools professional development services and digital textbooks as well as student assessments and publishes hard copy curriculumbased content for k schools in addition the company operates production studios that develop content for television service providers as well as websites it provides content through various distribution platforms comprising paytelevision freetoair and broadcast television websites digital distribution arrangements and content licensing agreements as well as various platforms that include brandaligned websites webnative networks online streaming mobile devices vod and broadband channels as of december   the company operated approximately  distribution feeds in  languages internationally discovery communications inc is headquartered in silver spring maryland detailed description one discovery placesilver spring md united states employees phone  corporatediscoverycom key executives for discovery communications inc mr david m zaslav ceo president  director age  total annual compensation m mr jeanbriac perrette ceo of discovery networks international and president of discovery networks international age  total annual compensation m mr bruce l campbell chief development distribution  legal officer age  total annual compensation m mr paul guagliardo chief commercial officer age  total annual compensation m ms adria alpert romm chief human resources  global diversity officer age  total annual compensation k compensation as of fiscal year  discovery communications inc key developments scripps family is in discussions for its potential sale jul   members of the family that controls scripps networks interactive inc nasdaqgssni are meeting today to discuss a potential sale amid takeover interest from discovery communications inc nasdaqgsdisca and viacom inc nasdaqgsvi