e largest content delivery networks he served as chief product officer and then chief executive officer of verizons joint venture with redbox for a subscription ott video service most recently ambeault oversaw the companys ott video products prior to his roles at verizon ambeault held technology product and marketing roles for seachange international ambeault is a member of the national television academy of arts and sciences technology committee he holds a bachelors degree from brandeis university and will be based in discoverys new york office  sharing and personal tools please select the service you want to use newsvine digg delicious stumbleupon technorati buzz favorites google reader public link please use the above public link if you want to share this noodl on another website close smartlinks  discovery communications inc  technology  finance  stock markets  security markets  stock markets  security markets  company news  company appointments  information technology  software  telecommunications services  arts and culture  entertainment  media  media and publishing  radio and television  broadcasting  television  broadcasting companies  börse frankfurt  börse berlin  börse düsseldorf  börse münchen  tradegate exchange  sp   nasdaq global select market  back  view original format copyright  public technologies inc  privacy policy  terms of use  contact discovery communications  wikipedia discovery communications from wikipedia the free encyclopedia jump to navigation search not to be confused with discover magazine discovery communications inc discovery communications headquarters at silver spring maryland the buildings logo has since changed type public company traded as nasdaq disca discb and disck nasdaq components disca and disck sp  components disca and disck isin usf usf industry mass media predecessor discovery holding company founded   years ago  as the discovery channel   years ago  as discovery communications founder john s hendricks headquarters silver spring maryland united states area served worldwide key people robert miron chairman david m zaslav president and ceo products broadcasting cable television and video streaming revenue us billion  us billion  operating income us billion  us billion  net income us billion  us  billion  number of employees   divisions list of divisions subsidiaries media alliance  allmedia  group nine media  lionsgate  website corporatediscoverycom discovery communications inc is an american global mass media and entertainment company based in silver spring maryland the company started as a single channel in  the discovery channel dci both produces original television programming and acquires content from producers worldwide the companys nonfiction lifestyle sports and kids programming is offered through paytv and freetoair networks among them discovery channel tlc investigation discovery animal planet own oprah winfrey network science velocity eurosport as well as directtoconsumer digital offerings including discovery’s go suite of apps discovery kids play and eurosport player discovery communications partnered with the world wildlife fund to fund conservation of  million acres of land for tigers in bhutan and india and to help double the worlds wild tiger population through project cat conserving acres for tigers in october  contents  corporate governance and history  divisions  discovery networks us  holdings  discovery networks international  group nine media  discovery education  history   hostage crisis  see also  references  external links corporate governance and historyedit nbcuniversal executive david zaslav was named president and ceo on november   in addition to zaslav current executives include adria alpert romm chief human resources  global diversity officer bruce campbell chief development distribution  legal officer  bill goodwyn president  ceo discovery education paul guyardo chief commercial officer john honeycutt chief technology officer david leavy chief corporate operations and communications officer jeanbriac jb perrette president discovery networks international gunnar wiedenfels chief financial officer  prior to september   dcis ownership consisted of three shareholders discovery holding company advancenewhouse communications which is owned with advance publications john s hendricks the companys founder on september   discovery holding company completed a restructuring plan discovery holdings ascent media business was spun off and the remaining businesses discovery communications llc and advancenewhouse communications were combined into a new holding company discovery communications inc the new fully public company and trades on the nasdaq stock market under the symbols disca discb and disck sec filings are submitted by the discovery holding company in may  the company announced a special dividend of shares of the companys series c common stock payable to holders of record of the companys series a common stock series b common stock and series c common stock as of the close of business on july   as a result of the dividend each holder of a share of the companys series a common stock series b common stock or series c common stock will receive one additional share of the companys series c common stock on or about august   through group nine media discovery connects with millennial audiences through digitalfirst brands nowthis thrillist the dodo source fed studios and seeker which has  billion streams per month in may  discovery and liberty global announced an agreement to form a  joint venture to acquire allmedia a producer and distributor of tv programming liberty global and discovery communications paid approximately  million for a  stake in lions gate entertainment group in november  liberty ceo mike fries joined the lions gate board of directors as part of the acquisition divisionsedit dci operates its businesses in the following groups discovery networks us discovery networks international discovery studios group discovery digital media and discovery education discovery networks usedit the companys namesake and flagship brand discovery channel first launched on june   in  discovery channels owners acquired the learning channel in october  discovery launched several new spinoff networks including animal planet and the digital cable channels discovery kids discovery travel  living discovery civilization and science channel this was followed by the  purchase of a  stake in travel channel and the  launches of discovery en español discovery wings and discovery health channel also in  discovery acquired a stake in the struggling cbs eye on people channel discovery eventually acquired the remainder of cbss stake leading to its january  relaunch as discovery people the network quietly folded in  being replaced by other discovery channels on providers on september   discovery communications bought the health channel and announced that it would be rebranded as fittv in  discovery relaunched discovery civilization as discovery times as part of a joint venture with the new york times in june  coinciding with discoverys th anniversary the company launched a  high definition channel known as discovery hd theater in march  discovery sold its stake in travel channel back to cox communications in exchange for the stake in discovery that cox owned cox would later sell the controlling interest in the channel to scripps networks interactive in  in june  discovery home was replaced by planet green a network devoted primarily to environmentalism and ecological living on january   discovery announced that it had entered into a joint venture with oprah winfreys harpo productions to relaunch discovery health as a new service own the oprah winfrey network in  in  discovery times was relaunched as investigation discovery a new brand that would be dedicated to true crime programs and documentaries on april   discovery announced a joint venture with hasbro to relaunch discovery kids as a new youth and familyoriented entertainment channel the channel ultimately named the hub launched on october   after multiple delays own officially launched on january   on october   due to the wider rollout of highdefinition feeds for mainstream cable channels hd theater was replaced by velocity a new upscale maleoriented channel focusing primarily on automotivethemed programming on may   planet green which had begun to abandon its original concept by  due to poor viewership was relaunched as destination america in october  discovery acquired controlling interest in the hub then hub network from hasbro and rebranded it as discovery family in december  discovery launched discovery go a tv everywhere service offering access to live streaming and ondemand content from discovery communications cable networks holdingsedit channel launch date us households as of august  notes discovery channel   million flagship network tlc   million acquired by discovery communications in may  previously known as the learning channel animal planet   million investigation discovery   million formerly discovery times discovery civilization own   million joint venture ownership with harpo productions velocity   million formerly discovery hd theater and hd theater science   million discovery family   million initially launched as discovery kids in  relaunched as the hub in  renamed hub network on  and rebranded as discovery family in   of the network is owned by hasbro american heroes channel   million formerly discovery wings military channel destination america   million formerly discovery home and leisure – discovery home – and planet green – discovery life   million merger of discovery health channel and fittv previously known as discovery fit  health discovery en español   million spanishlanguage version of the discovery channel unavailable in hd discovery familia   million unavailable in hd discovery networks internationaledit discovery networks asiapacific type subsidiary founded   years ago  headquarters  changi business park vista singapore area served asiapacific products broadcasting cable television and video streaming website asiadiscoverycom led by flagship network discovery channel discovery network international distributes international brands including discovery channel tlc id investigation discovery animal planet science turbo and eurosport the company employs an extensive localization strategy by offering customized schedules and programming in  languages worldwide via hundreds of distribution feeds discovery networks international has five regional operations spanning asiapacific central  eastern europe middle east and africa ceemea latin americaus hispanic northern europe and southern europe with regional headquarters in singapore warsaw miami london mumbai and milan in june  discovery communications won the multiplatform rights across europe to the olympic games from  to  discovery and eurosport promised more coverage than ever across screens to europes  million residents discovery paid  billion euros for the rights in  countries and renewed their longterm distribution agreement across  european countries with greatly expanded distribution rights over the longterm this deal includes discovery channel tlc id and eurosport the deal also includes digital rights discovery also signed deals with tdc  and sky  eurosport has also expanded its deal with the all england club to show all the wimbledon matches live in  additional countries it is a year deal that includes exclusive tv and digital rights this expands their tennis portfolio to show all four grand slams discovery communications has partnered with bamtech in november  to launch bamtech europe the technology provider will work with content owners broadcasters and other overthetop service providers in the region eurosport digital will be the first client in order to upgrade its suite of digital products to be powered by bamtech’s video platform in may  prosiebensat and discovery partnered on an ot