ry communications founder john s hendricks headquarters silver spring maryland united states area served worldwide key people robert miron chairman david m zaslav president and ceo products broadcasting cable television and video streaming revenue us billion  us billion  operating income us billion  us billion  net income us billion  us  billion  number of employees   divisions list of divisions subsidiaries media alliance  allmedia  group nine media  lionsgate  website corporatediscoverycom discovery communications inc is an american global mass media and entertainment company based in silver spring maryland the company started as a single channel in  the discovery channel dci both produces original television programming and acquires content from producers worldwide the companys nonfiction lifestyle sports and kids programming is offered through paytv and freetoair networks among them discovery channel tlc investigation discovery animal planet own oprah winfrey network science velocity eurosport as well as directtoconsumer digital offerings including discovery’s go suite of apps discovery kids play and eurosport player discovery communications partnered with the world wildlife fund to fund conservation of  million acres of land for tigers in bhutan and india and to help double the worlds wild tiger population through project cat conserving acres for tigers in october  contents  corporate governance and history  divisions  discovery networks us  holdings  discovery networks international  group nine media  discovery education  history   hostage crisis  see also  references  external links corporate governance and historyedit nbcuniversal executive david zaslav was named president and ceo on november   in addition to zaslav current executives include adria alpert romm chief human resources  global diversity officer bruce campbell chief development distribution  legal officer  bill goodwyn president  ceo discovery education paul guyardo chief commercial officer john honeycutt chief technology officer david leavy chief corporate operations and communications officer jeanbriac jb perrette president discovery networks international gunnar wiedenfels chief financial officer  prior to september   dcis ownership consisted of three shareholders discovery holding company advancenewhouse communications which is owned with advance publications john s hendricks the companys founder on september   discovery holding company completed a restructuring plan discovery holdings ascent media business was spun off and the remaining businesses discovery communications llc and advancenewhouse communications were combined into a new holding company discovery communications inc the new fully public company and trades on the nasdaq stock market under the symbols disca discb and disck sec filings are submitted by the discovery holding company in may  the company announced a special dividend of shares of the companys series c common stock payable to holders of record of the companys series a common stock series b common stock and series c common stock as of the close of business on july   as a result of the dividend each holder of a share of the companys series a common stock series b common stock or series c common stock will receive one additional share of the companys series c common stock on or about august   through group nine media discovery connects with millennial audiences through digitalfirst brands nowthis thrillist the dodo source fed studios and seeker which has  billion streams per month in may  discovery and liberty global announced an agreement to form a  joint venture to acquire allmedia a producer and distributor of tv programming liberty global and discovery communications paid approximately  million for a  stake in lions gate entertainment group in november  liberty ceo mike fries joined the lions gate board of directors as part of the acquisition divisionsedit dci operates its businesses in the following groups discovery networks us discovery networks international discovery studios group discovery digital media and discovery education discovery networks usedit the companys namesake and flagship brand discovery channel first launched on june   in  discovery channels owners acquired the learning channel in october  discovery launched several new spinoff networks including animal planet and the digital cable channels discovery kids discovery travel  living discovery civilization and science channel this was followed by the  purchase of a  stake in travel channel and the  launches of discovery en español discovery wings and discovery health channel also in  discovery acquired a stake in the struggling cbs eye on people channel discovery eventually acquired the remainder of cbss stake leading to its january  relaunch as discovery people the network quietly folded in  being replaced by other discovery channels on providers on september   discovery communications bought the health channel and announced that it would be rebranded as fittv in  discovery relaunched discovery civilization as discovery times as part of a joint venture with the new york times in june  coinciding with discoverys th anniversary the company launched a  high definition channel known as discovery hd theater in march  discovery sold its stake in travel channel back to cox communications in exchange for the stake in discovery that cox owned cox would later sell the controlling interest in the channel to scripps networks interactive in  in june  discovery home was replaced by planet green a network devoted primarily to environmentalism and ecological living on january   discovery announced that it had entered into a joint venture with oprah winfreys harpo productions to relaunch discovery health as a new service own the oprah winfrey network in  in  discovery times was relaunched as investigation discovery a new brand that would be dedicated to true crime programs and documentaries on april   discovery announced a joint venture with hasbro to relaunch discovery kids as a new youth and familyoriented entertainment channel the channel ultimately named the hub launched on october   after multiple delays own officially launched on january   on october   due to the wider rollout of highdefinition feeds for mainstream cable channels hd theater was replaced by velocity a new upscale maleoriented channel focusing primarily on automotivethemed programming on may   planet green which had begun to abandon its original concept by  due to poor viewership was relaunched as destination america in october  discovery acquired controlling interest in the hub then hub network from hasbro and rebranded it as discovery family in december  discovery launched discovery go a tv everywhere service offering access to live streaming and ondemand content from discovery communications cable networks holdingsedit channel launch date us households as of august  notes discovery channel   million flagship network tlc   million acquired by discovery communications in may  previously known as the learning channel animal planet   million investigation discovery   million formerly discovery times discovery civilization own   million joint venture ownership with harpo productions velocity   million formerly discovery hd theater and hd theater science   million discovery family   million initially launched as discovery kids in  relaunched as the hub in  renamed hub network on  and rebranded as discovery family in   of the network is owned by hasbro american heroes channel   million formerly discovery wings military channel destination america   million formerly discovery home and leisure – discovery home – and planet green – discovery life   million merger of discovery health channel and fittv previously known as discovery fit  health discovery en español   million spanishlanguage version of the discovery channel unavailable in hd discovery familia   million unavailable in hd discovery networks internationaledit discovery networks asiapacific type subsidiary founded   years ago  headquarters  changi business park vista singapore area served asiapacific products broadcasting cable television and video streaming website asiadiscoverycom led by flagship network discovery channel discovery network international distributes international brands including discovery channel tlc id investigation discovery animal planet science turbo and eurosport the company employs an extensive localization strategy by offering customized schedules and programming in  languages worldwide via hundreds of distribution feeds discovery networks international has five regional operations spanning asiapacific central  eastern europe middle east and africa ceemea latin americaus hispanic northern europe and southern europe with regional headquarters in singapore warsaw miami london mumbai and milan in june  discovery communications won the multiplatform rights across europe to the olympic games from  to  discovery and eurosport promised more coverage than ever across screens to europes  million residents discovery paid  billion euros for the rights in  countries and renewed their longterm distribution agreement across  european countries with greatly expanded distribution rights over the longterm this deal includes discovery channel tlc id and eurosport the deal also includes digital rights discovery also signed deals with tdc  and sky  eurosport has also expanded its deal with the all england club to show all the wimbledon matches live in  additional countries it is a year deal that includes exclusive tv and digital rights this expands their tennis portfolio to show all four grand slams discovery communications has partnered with bamtech in november  to launch bamtech europe the technology provider will work with content owners broadcasters and other overthetop service providers in the region eurosport digital will be the first client in order to upgrade its suite of digital products to be powered by bamtech’s video platform in may  prosiebensat and discovery partnered on an ottmobile service in germany   channel launch date international networks households as of notes discovery channel   million animal planet   million tlc  million investigation discovery  million eurosport acquired in   million discovery kids   million dmax   million launch  germany  uk  ireland  italy  asia discovery science   million discovery turbodiscovery turbo xtra   million quest  million eurosport   million discovery home  health   million discovery communications also operates living channel and food tv in new zealand group nine mediaedit main article group nine media in october  discovery announced a minority investment in and strategic partnership with group nine media – a new media holding company consisting of thrillist nowthis the dodo and discovery’s digital network seeker and sourcefed studios creating a digitalfirst media company in us with  billion monthly video views discovery educationedit discovery education is a division which offers standardsbased digital content for k in  discovery education expanded its reach by acquiring espresso group ltd serving  million educators and over  million students discovery educations services are in half of us classrooms over  percent of all primary schools in the uk and more than  countries historyedit after acquiring the learning channel now tlc in may  discovery announced plans in november  to launch four new channels including animal planet and what would later become science channel in june  discovery communications launched the first  hd network in the united states discovery hd theater hd feeds would later be launched for its networks in the us and globally as the technology took hold in living rooms on march   discovery revealed that it owned the rights to several patents related to ebooks in announcing a patent infringement lawsuit against amazoncom maker of the kindle ebook reading device the patents were originally developed by the companys founder john hendricks the specific patent in question in the suit was applied for in  but issued in late  on december   discovery announced it had taken a  minority interest share with tf group in sports broadcaster eurosport valued at € million us million on january   discovery became the majority shareholder in eurosport taking a  share of the company in  discovery closed a transaction to acquire  of eurosport in april  discovery announced another digital investment in the form of a partnership with brian grazer and ron howard to launch digital studio new form digital in may  discovery and liberty global announced an agreement to form a  joint venture to acquire allmedia a producer and distributor of tv programming in august  discovery communications launched discovery vr a crosscompany virtual reality offering after announcing its plans in may in december  discovery launched the companys first us tve streaming service discovery go connecting viewers with live and ondemand access to shows and series from several us networks in the discovery portfolio – discovery channel tlc animal planet investigation discovery science channel velocity destination america american heroes channel and discovery life in q  discovery shifted its strategy entirely towards digital media international markets and diversifying content in order to make up for shrinking cable network viewers they have invested in directtoconsumer offerings and digital distribution channels  of their revenue was through affiliates this quarter they took a minority stake in chinese mcn vs media a company that has  million subscribers in china with more than  monthly video views october  discovery purchased a minority stake in group nine media – a new media holding company consisting of thrillist media group nowthis media the dodo and discovery’s digital network seeker for  million discovery will have the option in two years time to acquire a controlling stake  hostage crisisedit on september   the dci headquarters was the site of a hostage taking a lone gunman identified as james j lee armed with two starter pistols and an explosive device took three people hostage inside of the discovery communications headquarters in silver spring maryland prompting an evacuation of the building lees motive was believed to have been grounded in environmental activism lee had previously been arrested in  while protesting in front of the same site the national consortium for the study of terrorism and responses to terrorism start at the university of maryland has since labeled the crime a terrorist attack the incident began at  pm et when yearold james jay lee entered the building with two starter pistols and fired a single round at the ceiling of the lobby the montgomery county police department mcpd confirmed that lee had an explosive device and was holding three people hostage in the lobby the building was placed on lockdown and most of the  employees were evacuated children from a day care center inside were safely removed to a nearby mcdonalds restaurant on colesville rd lee was shot dead by an mcpd swat team at  pm et after the hostages made a run to escape the remaining hostages were immediately freed the incident was described by the fbi as the first instance of a wouldbe suicide bomber taking hostages in the united states james jay lee c  – september   was an environmental protester who in  was given six months of supervised probation and fined  after he was arrested during a protest outside the discovery communications headquarters lee had published criticisms of the network in an online manifesto at savetheplanetprotestcom among which was a demand for the company to cease the broadcasting of television series displaying or encouraging the birth of parasitic human infants and the false heroics behind those actions his manifesto also railed against immigration pollution and anchor baby filth leading commentators such as mark potok of the southern poverty law center to decry lee as an ecofascist lees opinions were dominated by malthusian analysis though he also cited works ranging from daniel quinns novel my ishmael to former us vice president al gores documentary an inconvenient truth the washington post credited the twitter community for initially breaking the story see alsoedit discovery networks ceemea discovery networks emea discovery networks northern europe national geographic society referencesedit  a b c d e f discovery communications inc  annual report form k xbrl united states securities and exchange commission february     russian government approves discoverys joint venture with national media group the hollywood reporter retrieved    a b spangler todd  october  discovery investing  million to merge thrillist nowthis the dodo in new digital venture retrieved  november    discovery launches tv everywhere service with one app instead of  retrieved  july    bbc  bbc and discovery communications sign longterm olympic games partnership  media centre wwwbbccouk retrieved    discovery wwf partner for project cat retrieved    ahrens frank november   discovery appoints new chief the washington post   leadership discoverycom   adria alpert romm adria alpert romm  discovery communications  bruce campbell discovery communications   bill goodwyn  discovery communications   paul guyardo discovery communications paul guyardo discovery communications  john honeycutt  cto discovery communications john honeycutt  david c leavy   jeanbriac jb perrette jeanbriac jb perrette  andreeva nellie  discovery communications hires gunnar wiedenfels as new chief financial officer deadline retrieved    httpswebarchiveorgwebhttpmoneycnncomnewsnewsfeedsarticlesnewstexafxhtm archived from the original on december    missing or empty title help  information statement discovery holding company us securities and exchange commission  inc discovery communications discovery communications announces special dividend of series c common stock wwwprnewswirecom retrieved   